John R. Egan | Managing Partner
�After signing a term sheet with Egan-Managed Capital, several other interested investors expressed a strong desire to alter the terms of the deal. Egan-Managed Capital never wavered. They have been straightforward, honest, and have kept all cards on the table from start to finish.� 
 
-Nick d'Arbeloff 
  President & CEO
  Conjoin, Inc.
"We couldn't ask for a better partner than Egan-Managed Capital. They provide a great combination of real-world experience with a true understanding of the start-up environment. As a result, they help companies like Genalytics realize their full potential in the market."
 
-Doug Newell
  President & CEO
  Genalytics, Inc.
�Egan-Managed Capital brought to Novera a pragmatic business perspective and operational experience. And they're great to work with.� 
 
-Dave Power
  President & CEO
  Novera Software 
�Egan-Managed Capital had the foresight and vision to recognize the opportunity as well as the transformation necessary to take the Company to the next level. Jack and Alex fostered our entrepreneurial spirit with both their commitment to the business as well as their advice and counsel.� 
 
-Mike Byers 
  President & COO 
  HighRoads 
�We have been lucky to have Jack Egan as the lead director of the NetScout Board for almost 5 years. In my 25 years of experience in the high tech industry, I have yet to come across anyone who can match the practical and in-depth experience of Jack in almost all areas of a company�s operation. He has been a great mentor for the entire management team on matters ranging from sales operation and strategic planning to financial controls, corporate governance, HR and compliance."
 




-Anil Singhal 
 Co-founder & CEO

 Netscout

As a Managing Partner, Mr. Egan plays an active role in the investment process at Egan-Managed Capital and is available to support the growth and recruiting activities of Egan-Managed Capital portfolio companies. He currently serves on the Board of Directors of former portfolio company NetScout Systems, and is a Board Member at both EMC Corporation and VMware, Inc. He formerly served as a Board Director for EPiCON (acquired by Northern Telecom, NYSE: NT), CenterStone Software (acquired by Manhattan Software), HighGround Systems (acquired by Sun Microsystems), Lineo, Monetrics (acquired by JM Family Enterprises), Novera Software (acquired by Mercator Software, NASDAQ: MCTR), Healthrageous, HighRoads, and Caldera Systems (NASDAQ: CALD). 

 
John Egan co-founded Egan-Managed Capital during a sabbatical from EMC Corporation. Prior to his sabbatical he was Executive Vice President of Sales & Marketing for several years where he directed the development of EMC�s sales force and market positioning. During his tenure, the sales organization missed only one out of 54 quarterly sales quotas while growing the business from $3 million to nearly $3 billion in annual sales. He returned to EMC at the request of the Company�s Board in early 1998 to assume a 10-month role as Executive Vice President of Products where he managed marketing, manufacturing and product development through a transition to a new organizational structure. Having achieved the Board�s objectives, he retired from active employment at EMC at the end of 1998. He holds degrees in marketing and computer science from Boston College. 


