Executive Profile
John R. Egan  Managing Partner, Carruth Management, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships59--
Background

		Mr. John R. Egan, also known as Jack, founded Egan-Managed Capital in October 1998. Mr. Egan has been Managing Partner of Egan-Managed Capital since February 1997 and General Partner since October 1998 and is its Founding Managing Partner. He has been a Principal in a venture capital firm since October 1998. Mr. Egan has been a Managing Partner at Carruth Management, LLC, which he founded in October 1998. He works at SCO Group Inc. He worked at Shiva Corporation. From ... April 1983 to September 1998, he has served in various capacities at EMC Corporation. From May 1997 to September 1998, he served as an Executive Vice President of Products and Offerings of EMC Corporation. From January 1992 to June 1996, he served as an Executive Vice President, Sales and Marketing of EMC. From October 1986 to January 1992, he served in a number of executive positions with EMC, including Executive Vice President, Operations and Executive Vice President, International Sales. He resigned as an executive officer of EMC in September 1998 and as an employee of EMC in July 2002. He has been the Non-Executive Chairman at Progress Software Corporation since December 2012 and has been its Director since September 6, 2011. He has been a Director of Verint Systems Inc. since August 16, 2012. He has been Director at EMC Corporation since May 1992 and Platform Computing Inc. since June 2009. He has been an Independent Director of NetScout Systems, Inc. since October 2000 and has been its Lead Independent Director since 2001. He serves as a Director at AllVertical, Caldera Systems. He serves as Director of IONA Technologies Limited. He serves as a Member of the Board of Trustees at Children's Hospital Trust and serves as Director for four privately-held companies. He also serves in a variety of leadership roles within the Board of Directors of several privately held technology companies, including HighRoads Corporation. He served as Chairman of the Board of Centerstone Software, Inc. He served as Director of The TSG Group, Inc. He served as a Director of VMware, Inc. since April 2007 until September 06, 2016. He served as Director of Data Domain, Inc. since July 2009. He served as a Director at Healthrageous, Inc. and Platform Computing Corporation since June 2009. He served as Director of Embedix, Inc. since January 2000 and HighRoads, Inc., since May 12, 2005. He served as Director of Novera Software, Inc., and Epicon, Inc. He serves as Trustee of Boston College. He holds B.S. in Marketing and Computer Science from Boston College in 1979.Read Full Background




