 Obituary			



 Service Details
			




        John R. Egan, 57, of Aberdeen, New Jersey, passed away peacefully surrounded by his loving family on Saturday, September 3, 2016 at Bayshore Community Hospital in Holmdel, New Jersey.  John was born on June 27, 1959 in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, and was raised in Warminster, Pennsylvania.  In 1976, he and his family moved to Toms River, New Jersey, and in 1996, he and his wife, Frances, settled in the Matawan/Aberdeen area.  He had a love for hiking and was an avid outdoors man.  John was also a partner at Excel Thermal Spray company.  He was predeceased by his father, Ramsey Michael Egan.  John is survived by his devoted wife, Frances (Franco) Egan, his beloved mother, Mary (Lanik) Egan Mayer, his loving sisters, Carol Bornstein and her husband, Alan, of St. Louis, Missouri, Susan Egan of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, and Janice Egan and her life-long companion, Jack McGuire, of Chester Springs, Pennsylvania.  John is also survived by his cherished nieces and nephew, Claire, Mitchell, and Natalie Bornstein, his brother-in-law, Peter Franco and his wife, Glenda, and his sisters-in-law, Mary Ellen Thomas, and Margaret Graham.  He will be deeply missed, but never forgotten.
       Arrangements were entrusted to the Shore Point Funeral Home and Cremation Services, Inc., 3269 State Route/Highway 35 North, Hazlet ,New Jersey 07730.  In respect of John's wishes, he will be privately cremated.  Donations in loving memory of John to the Popcorn Park Zoo, would be greatly appreciated.  To donate, please visit, www.ahscares.org.   For information, directions, or to send condolences to the family, please visit, www.shorepointfh.com.












